<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
The species was described from Nepal, ex herb. Hooker (P00606414) (see link to the specimen https://science.mnhn.fr/institution/mnhn/collection/p/item/p00606414) and the type material bears a plant fragment collected at the flowering stage. This name has never been mentioned in the recent floristic and taxonomic accounts except the Flora of the USSR (
<bibRefCitation author="Iljin, MM" editor="Shishkin, BK" journalOrPublisher="6. Akademiya Nauk, Moscow-Leningrad" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" pagination="2 - 354" refId="B47" refString="Iljin, MM, 1936. Chenopodiaceae. In: Shishkin, BK, Ed., Flora of USSR, Vol. 6. Akademiya Nauk, Moscow-Leningrad: 2 - 354" title="Chenopodiaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of USSR, Vol." year="1936">Iljin 1936</bibRefCitation>
), where it was synonymised with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="D. Don" authorityYear="1825" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Chenopodium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Chenopodium giganteum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="giganteum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Chenopodium giganteum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="C." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. bengalense" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="bengalense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C. bengalense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). However, the protologue of C. 
<taxonomicName family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="C." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="hookerianum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="hookerianum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">hookerianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Moquin-Tandon, A" editor="de Candolle, A" journalOrPublisher="13 (2). Masson, Paris" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" pagination="43 - 219" refId="B71" refString="Moquin-Tandon, A, 1849. Salsolaceae [Chenopodiaceae]. In: de Candolle, A, Ed., Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis, Vol. 13(2). Masson, Paris: 43 - 219" title="Salsolaceae [Chenopodiaceae]." volumeTitle="Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis, Vol." year="1849">Moquin-Tandon 1849</bibRefCitation>
) and a fragment of the type specimen do not demonstrate the features of the species described by Moquin well (plant height, seed characters etc.). We are still not sure how to treat 
<taxonomicName family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="C." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. hookerianum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="hookerianum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C. hookerianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
